-- Walgreen CEO set to add chairman role in July
-- 
-- Thu Apr 12, 2007 10:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/12/us-walgreen-chairman-idUSWEN641120070412

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Walgreen Co. ( WAG.N ), one of the largest U.S. drugstore chains, said on Thursday that President and Chief Executive Jeffrey Rein will become chairman on July 11, when Chairman David Bernauer retires from the board after working with the company for 40 years. 

 Rein, 55, will still serve as CEO. Gregory Wasson, 48, the president of Walgreens Health Services, the company's managed care division, will become president and chief operating officer as of May 1. Among other changes, Deerfield, Illinois-based Walgreen said that Chief Information Officer Trent Taylor will replace Wasson on May 1 as president of Walgreens Health Services.